  <ul class="normal">
   <li>Obstacle Course: Help your children plan and create a safe course they can go over, under, around, and through.</li>
   <li>Balloon Volleyball: Players on either side of a taut string bat a balloon back and forth.</li>
   <li>Tumbling Tornadoes: Let your kids tumble as they wish on a safe, soft surface.</li>
   <li>Cross the Brook: Using tape or chalk, make two lines that are a foot apart. Participants hop or run across the "brook." They can also look for ways to build bridges.</li>
   <li>Cooperative Race:<i> </i>Partners link a part of their bodies together (such as elbows or hands) and run to a finish line.</li>
  </ul>
